    "Our results also show that there are no consistent patterns of which LLM and what prompts work the best for what types of data.",
    "OpenAI's models are not open-sourced, making the use and explanation of the model output opaque for researchers in the health domain.",
    "Second, recent research has revealed the risk of LLMs in leaking training data, which could be particularly concerning due to the sensitive nature of health-related data.",
    "30 While OpenAI stated that user input will only be stored on their servers and not be used for training their models, patients and the public who produced the health-related social media data may still perceive this as risky.",
